            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>ginger & shallot mix</strong> to the pot with the brown rice (reserve the pan!), then add the<strong> pho stock</strong>,<strong> lime leaf[ves]</strong>,<strong> chopped green beans </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium-high and cook, covered<strong> </strong>for an initial 2-3 min or until the green beans are tender</p><p>Once tender, add the <strong>spinach</strong> and<strong> carrot ribbons </strong>and cook, covered, for a final 1-2 min or until the spinach has wilted – this is your <strong>Vietnamese-style rice broth</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
